verses.roman:
ācārya gosāñira guṇa-mahimā apāra
jīva-kīṭa kothāya pāibeka tāra pāra

synonyms: ācārya gosāñira—of Advaita Ācārya; guṇa-mahimā—the glory of the attributes; apāra—unfathomable; jīva-kīṭa—a living being who is just like a worm; kothāya—where; pāibeka—will get; tāra—of that; pāra—the other side.
translation: The glory and attributes of Advaita Ācārya are unlimited. How can the insignificant living entities fathom them?
